 Features archive 

 
 





 

  
            
           
            
       
          May 11, 2016 
           Helping people, improving lives through informatics
  
          Professor Rebecca Black joins the ICS faculty where she will continue her research into bridging education and IT.        
      
    
                    
 
            
           
            
       
          May 3, 2016 
           ICS receives Excellence in Promoting Women in Undergraduate Computing Award from NCWIT
  
          The Google-funded NEXT award provides $100,000 for ICS to continue working with underrepresented groups to pursue technology-related degrees.        
      
    
                    
 
            
           
            
       
          April 25, 2016 
           CS undergrad's business makes Inc.’s 2016 list of Coolest College Startups
  
          Junior Nick Nguyen is recognized for his startup CubeForme, a 3-D printing subscription-box service.        
      
    
                    
 
            
           
            
       
          April 13, 2016 
           Putting theory into practice
  
          Computer science major Andres Vourakis prepares for a second season of his STEM-focused web series Stembility.        
      
    
                    
 
            
           
            
       
          March 3, 2016 
           Jessica Utts: An ambassador for statistics
  
          As ASA president, Utts looks forward to forging new relationships with statisticians and promoting the field worldwide.





        
      
    
                    
 
            
           
            
       
          February 18, 2016 
           Unlocking the potential of deep learning
  
          Pierre Baldi leads ICS’s machine learning research, which assists particle physics experiments at CERN.





        
      
    


  
 
 
  
